It was difficult to derive whether they have invited nostalgia over tea or whether they intentionally accepted an invite into the old memory lanes, year after year, without fail, together.
A ritual spanning over a decade, two cups of chai, roses wrapped in torn newspaper, a park bench, a setting sun, and two women with their shared love and lover—well, the last evening of the year has looked the same for Maya and Meera over the last 10 years.

