Rituals and religion, they say, can bind and break even strangers in ways the world can only gasp at! The reason is fairly simple: it's either love or hatred towards one higher source, a being, an entity, and if you add a chapter of a lover into the mix of this love/hatred recipe, you serve the world with a dish that cannot be forgotten.


