Maya and Meera share quite a few commonalities apart from a lover!
They share the color pink—one that shone as a bindi and bruise and decorated their body equally fine.
They share the pain of broken promises, which now bleeds through their palms, drowning the lines of love and destiny.
They share the grief of lost hope, which walked out of their lives, leaving them bound to the entrance between old endings and new beginnings.
They share the feeling of not being chosen: by love and lover, for he chose death—a ritual and religion that neither of them could devote themselves to.


