Love felt vicious; it felt dark and consuming.
It felt like a taker of all things light and bright.
But love was also generous; it gave back more than it took.
just in a different face and skin
Love gave courage to two hearts who surrendered their lives holding shared pieces of one heart that stopped beating 10 years ago.
Love gave companionship and a grieving partner to Maya and Meera in the form of a ritual that they carved together.
Love offered silence and peace to accept the storms that uprooted Maya and Meera only to root them in a garden.
Love turned a life sentence into life for Maya and Meera through rituals and roses.



